-- India's jewellery firms surge after cbank eases gold import norms
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Wed May 21, 2014 11:43PM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, May 22 (Reuters) - Shares in Titan Co Ltd <TITN.NS> surged 9.99 percent in pre-open trading on Thursday after India's central bank eased gold import rules by allowing seven more private agencies to ship the precious metal.

The move by the Reserve Bank of India, announced late on Wednesday, could augment supplies of gold, according to analysts. [ID:nL3N0O7465] Among other jewellery companies Gitanjali Gems <GTGM.NS> gained 13.6 percent, Rajesh Exports Ltd <REXP.NS> rose 6.7 percent.